      • collection_array

        protected void collection_array(ConvertToken<java.util.Collection,java.lang.Object> token)
        Replace the elements on the ConvertToken.output from the given token. All from the given ConvertToken.input. If the output is null, or have a type different than the class at ConvertToken.outputClazz. Or have length other than the length of the ConvertToken.input. Then the output will be replaced with a new output with the class of ConvertToken.outputClazz.
        Parameters:
        token - the conversion instance that holds the variables of this conversion
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the given 'token' or 'token.input' is null

        protected void recurs_object(ConvertToken<Recurse,java.lang.Object> token)

        Parameters:
        token - the conversion instance that holds the variables of this conversion
        Throws:

      • string_object

        protected void string_object(ConvertToken<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> token)
                      throws java.lang.ReflectiveOperationException
        Try to construct a new object of the value of the given ConvertToken.input with type of the ConvertToken.outputClazz. Using ether a method with a signature equals to 'valueOf(String)'. Or a constructor with a signature equals to '(String)'.
        Parameters:
        token - the conversion instance that holds the variables of this conversion
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the given 'token' or 'input' is null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the 'outputClass' don't have a 'valueOf(String)' method nor a (String) constructor
        java.lang.ReflectiveOperationException - if any exception occurred while trying to construct the output object
